---

<BaseLayout
  title="Porta Potty Rental Cost Guide 2025 | Pricing & Rates"
  description="Complete guide to porta potty rental costs in 2025. Compare prices for standard units, luxury trailers, ADA accessible, and more. Get accurate pricing estimates."
>
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <Breadcrumb items={breadcrumbs} />

    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
        Porta Potty Rental Cost Guide
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        Understand what you'll pay for portable restroom rentals. Prices vary by location, type, and rental duration.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Quick Stats -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-primary-500 to-primary-600 rounded-2xl p-6 text-white text-center">
        <div class="text-4xl font-bold mb-2">$75-$150</div>
        <div class="text-primary-100">Standard Unit / Day</div>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-500 to-blue-600 rounded-2xl p-6 text-white text-center">
        <div class="text-4xl font-bold mb-2">$175-$400</div>
        <div class="text-blue-100">Standard Unit / Month</div>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-green-500 to-green-600 rounded-2xl p-6 text-white text-center">
        <div class="text-4xl font-bold mb-2">$50-$150</div>
        <div class="text-green-100">Typical Delivery Fee</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Pricing Table -->
    <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-xl overflow-hidden mb-12">
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full">
          <thead class="bg-gray-50 border-b border-gray-200">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-6 py-4 text-left text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">Type</th>
              <th class="px-6 py-4 text-center text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">Daily</th>
              <th class="px-6 py-4 text-center text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">Weekly</th>
              <th class="px-6 py-4 text-center text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">Monthly</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-200">
            {pricingData.map((item) => (
              <tr class="hover:bg-gray-50">
                <td class="px-6 py-5">
                  <div class="flex items-center">
                    <span class="text-2xl mr-3">{item.icon}</span>
                    <div>
                      <div class="font-semibold text-gray-900">{item.type}</div>
                      <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">{item.description}</div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </td>
                <td class="px-6 py-5 text-center font-medium text-gray-900">{item.daily}</td>
                <td class="px-6 py-5 text-center font-medium text-gray-900">{item.weekly}</td>
                <td class="px-6 py-5 text-center font-medium text-green-600">{item.monthly}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Factors Affecting Price -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 text-center">
        What Affects Your Price
      </h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        {factors.map((factor) => (
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-200 p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
            <div class="text-3xl mb-3">{factor.icon}</div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">{factor.title}</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">{factor.description}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- What's Included -->
    <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-2xl p-8 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">What's Typically Included</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-green-600 mb-3 flex items-center">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 mr-2" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
              <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
            </svg>
            Usually Included
          </h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600">
            <li>Weekly cleaning and servicing</li>
            <li>Waste pump-out and disposal</li>
            <li>Toilet paper restocking</li>
            <li>Hand sanitizer refills</li>
            <li>Deodorizer treatment</li>
            <li>Basic delivery and pickup</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-orange-600 mb-3 flex items-center">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 mr-2" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
              <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M8.257 3.099c.765-1.36 2.722-1.36 3.486 0l5.58 9.92c.75 1.334-.213 2.98-1.742 2.98H4.42c-1.53 0-2.493-1.646-1.743-2.98l5.58-9.92zM11 13a1 1 0 11-2 0 1 1 0 012 0zm-1-8a1 1 0 00-1 1v3a1 1 0 002 0V6a1 1 0 00-1-1z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
            </svg>
            Often Extra Cost
          </h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600">
            <li>Rush delivery (same-day/next-day)</li>
            <li>Long-distance delivery fees</li>
            <li>Extra servicing (2-3x per week)</li>
            <li>Holiday or weekend delivery</li>
            <li>Damage/cleaning fees</li>
            <li>Stairs or difficult placement</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Tips Section -->
    <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 p-8 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Tips for Getting the Best Price</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="flex items-start">
          <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-100 text-primary-600 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold mr-4">1</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Book Early</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Reserve 2-3 weeks ahead, especially for peak season. Last-minute bookings cost more.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start">
          <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-100 text-primary-600 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold mr-4">2</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Get Multiple Quotes</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Prices vary significantly between providers. Compare at least 3 quotes.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start">
          <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-100 text-primary-600 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold mr-4">3</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Choose Monthly Rates</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">For rentals over 2 weeks, monthly rates offer 40-60% savings vs. daily rates.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start">
          <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-100 text-primary-600 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold mr-4">4</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Ask About Bundles</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Renting multiple units or adding hand wash stations? Ask for package discounts.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-primary-600 to-blue-700 rounded-2xl p-8 text-center text-white">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Ready to Get an Exact Quote?</h2>
      <p class="text-blue-100 mb-6 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Use our calculator to estimate your needs, then find providers in your area.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/calculator" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center bg-white text-primary-600 px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold hover:bg-blue-50 transition-colors">
          Use Calculator
        </a>
        <a href="/states" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center border-2 border-white text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold hover:bg-white/10 transition-colors">
          Find Providers
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- SEO Content -->
    <div class="mt-12 prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <h2>Understanding Porta Potty Rental Costs</h2>
      <p>
        Portable toilet rental prices depend on many factors, but understanding the basics will help you budget
        accurately for your event or job site. Most providers offer daily, weekly, and monthly rates, with
        longer rentals providing better per-day value.
      </p>

      <h3>Standard vs. Luxury Units</h3>
      <p>
        Standard porta potties are the most affordable option, typically running $75-$150 per day or $175-$400 per month.
        These include basic amenities like toilet paper and hand sanitizer. Luxury restroom trailers with
        climate control, flushing toilets, and running water cost significantly more ($500-$1,500+ per day)
        but provide a much better guest experience for weddings and upscale events.
      </p>

      <h3>Hidden Costs to Watch For</h3>
      <p>
        Always ask about delivery fees, pickup fees, and servicing frequency. Some providers include delivery
        within a certain radius, while others charge $50-$150 or more. Rush deliveries (same-day or next-day)
        typically cost extra. For multi-day events, confirm whether daily servicing is included or extra.
      </p>

      <h3>OSHA Requirements for Construction Sites</h3>
      <p>
        Construction sites must comply with OSHA regulations for portable toilets. The number required depends
        on the number of workers: 1 toilet for up to 20 workers, 2 for 20-35 workers, and so on. Failing to
        provide adequate facilities can result in fines.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
